## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [CS9388]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;In the absence of vernalization, the double mutant flowered at the same time as the fca-1 single mutant.
   - [CS9388]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Reduced response of fca-1 to vernalization; under typical long-day (16h) photoperiods, vrn1-1 fca-1 flowers with about 25 leaves without vernalization and with about 20 leaves after vernalization; the diameter of the vegetative rosette is smaller than fca-1 alone; older leaves develop grayish-brown necrotic lesions.
   - [vrn1-2]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;No delay in flowering but reduction in vernalization response.
   - [vrn1-2 fca-1]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Strong delay in flowering and vernalization response.
